answer_found_by_llm: There was no process ID (PID) clearly associated with any file that exhibits suspicious behavior. Our volatility analysis (using filescan and process listing on the Win7 memory dump) did not reveal any document file, temporary executable, or atypical process (e.g. winword.exe) that could be linked to the suspicious email/document. This suggests that if the malicious activity occurred, it did not leave behind an obvious PID-to-file association in the captured memory.
